para.verbatim:
Matches if current position is at the beginning of a line within the parse string
Example::
test = '''\ AAA this line AAA and this line AAA but not this one B AAA and definitely not this one '''
for t in (LineStart() + 'AAA' + restOfLine).search_string(test): print(t)
prints::
['AAA', ' this line'] ['AAA', ' and this line']
